category=Getting Started
description=<p>The Internet Image Importer application allows you to enter the URL (or web address) to any web page.  It then downloads all the images from that page, and can either display those images sequentially as a slide show, save them as individual cards in a stack, or directly copy them all into a directory.  The scripts show you how to download from the Internet and how to parse an HTML page to extract the images.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Video Tutorial shows you how to use this Sample Project, and how to take it apart to understand how it works or copy portions of it for use in your own applications.  The PDF contains the same information as the Video, in printable form.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Lucida Grande" size="11"><a href="video:Internet Image Importer">Click here to go to the corresponding video and PDF</a></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>We recommend you to have explored the introductory video tutorials so you have a basic understanding of how Revolution works before you start on the Sample Projects.</p>
level=3
name=Internet Image Importer
title=Internet Image Importer -  importing all the images from a web page
topics=<p>The key topics covered in this Project are:</p>\n<p>   - How to download images from a web site</p>\n<p>   - How to display images you download</p>\n<p>   - How to save images you download to a file</p>\n<p>   - How to allow the user to enter a URL into a text box</p>\n<p>   - How to parse HTML to find image tags (using chunk expressions)</p>